title: For Sale:  Functioning PPSH-41 7.62x25 built on IO Receiver PPSH 41 1941 Drum
postcontent:
For sale is a PPSH-41 that has been converted to a striker configuration for legal semi-auto use.  The receiver was manufactured by Inter-Ordnance for their SR-41 project, but sold as an extra when the project was cancelled.  The receiver is well made, but the weld around the front sight isn't pretty. The rear spring latch on these was welded shut, so the action must be opened by removing out the hinge pin.  

Functioning:  This rifle works fine with stick mags, but doesn't feed reliably from the drum I  have.  Looks like an issue with the feed lips on this particular drum, but I'm not sure since I never tested it with any others.  If you like to tinker then this is the rifle for you. As such, it is being sold with the understanding that it is essentially a parts kit but for the price of parts, you get a rare complete receiver and a functioning gun that you can go out and shoot.  Must be transferred through an FFL.

title: For Sale/Trade:  2006 Suzuki LTR450r
postcontent:
I have an 06 LTR450 that I am wanting to sell. I bought it a few months ago blown up from someone that I knew with intentions of rebuilding it. I had no idea what was actually wrong with it when I bought it, I just knew that it shut off on him after running it hard. After I dug into it, I saw that it jumped time, bent 3 valves, destroyed the piston, and grooved the cylinder.

I just went through the bottom end. I split the cases, got the metal shavings out of the bottom end, checked the oil pump, transmission...etc. I put new main bearings in and a new timing chain in it. The bottom end is ready to go, just needs a PISTON and a CYLINDER HEAD. I bought another cylinder for it since the old one was grooved. It will come with the old cylinder as well.
